      "comment": "MAURLEN BOY (2) should find this easier than his last attempt at Menangle when he drew very wide. Did well to come from the outside and finish second to a Group 1 winner at this circuit and distance prior. Perfectly drawn so should get his chance. CHICAGO BART (9) has been racing very well and registered another success last time out, scoring by close 5 metres at this circuit and distance. Shouldn't spend a penny from this draw and the sprint lane may come in handy. Can continue the strong form. BAXTER RED (10) was only beaten 3m when he came from this barrier first up here last month. Should be at his peak now and did a good to place last week. HUNTER SHANNON (8) draws wide but is going well with a win and two placings from his last three starts here.",
